# SVG2ICO

![SVG2ICO](https://github.com/username/svg2ico/blob/main/assets/logo.png) <!-- Consider adding a logo image to your repo -->

A simple command-line tool to batch convert SVG files to ICO (Windows icon) format.

## 📋 Overview

SVG2ICO converts SVG vector graphics into ICO files that can be used for:
- Windows application icons
- Website favicons (favicon.ico)
- File association icons
- Any other use case requiring ICO format

This tool maintains image quality by first converting SVGs to high-resolution PNG files (256x256) and then to ICO format, ensuring crisp icons at all sizes.

## 🚀 Installation

### Option 1: Install globally (recommended)

```bash
npm install -g svg2ico
```

This makes the `svg2ico` command available system-wide.

### Option 2: Clone the repository

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/username/svg2ico.git

# Navigate to the project directory
cd svg2ico

# Install dependencies
npm install
```

## 🔧 Configuration

You can customize the default input and output directories by editing lines 9-10 in the `batch-convert.js` file:

```javascript
// Default paths (edit these to match your preferred locations)
const DEFAULT_INPUT_FOLDER = "../Desktop/Design/icons";
const DEFAULT_OUTPUT_FOLDER = "../Desktop/Design/converted-ico-files";
```

## 💻 Usage

### Command Line Interface

```bash
svg2ico [input-folder] [output-folder]
```

#### Parameters:

| Parameter | Description | Default Value |
|-----------|-------------|---------------|
| `input-folder` | Directory containing SVG files to convert | `"../Desktop/Design/icons"` |
| `output-folder` | Directory where ICO files will be saved | `"../Desktop/Design/converted-ico-files"` |

### Desktop Shortcut (Windows)

The repository includes a batch file (`run-svg2ico.bat`) with the following content:

```batch
@echo off
echo Running SVG to ICO Converter...
svg2ico
echo Conversion complete! Press any key to exit...
pause > nul
```

To create a desktop shortcut: ```(Windows only)```

1. Right-click on your desktop
2. Select "New" > "Shortcut"
3. Copy the path to `run-svg2ico.bat` file (from your cloned repo)
4. Click "Next" and give your shortcut a name (e.g., "SVG to ICO Converter")
5. Click "Finish"

Now you can run the converter with a single click!

## 📝 Examples

### Convert SVGs from a specific folder:

```bash
svg2ico ./my-svg-folder ./new-ico-folder
```

### Convert using default folders: 

> [!TIP] Default folders must be added in the `batch-convert.js` file


```bash
svg2ico
```

### Process flow:

1. SVG files are read from the input folder
2. Each SVG is converted to a high-quality PNG (256x256)
3. PNGs are then converted to ICO format
4. ICO files are saved to the output folder

## 📦 Dependencies

This tool relies on the following npm packages:

- [sharp](https://www.npmjs.com/package/sharp) - High-performance SVG to PNG conversion
- [png-to-ico](https://www.npmjs.com/package/png-to-ico) - Efficient PNG to ICO conversion

## 🔍 Troubleshooting

### Common issues:

- **Error: Cannot find module 'sharp'**: Run `npm install` in the project directory
- **Permission errors**: Run with administrator privileges or adjust folder permissions
- **Output folder not found**: The tool will attempt to create the output folder if it doesn't exist

